The paper deals with a problem related to hypergraphs and their properties, which falls under the scope of computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new variant of the VC-dimension, which is a concept related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.DM). The paper also presents an explicit construction of epsilon-t-nets, which involves combinatorial and algorithmic techniques, falling under the scope of computational complexity (cs.CC).
